com.teamdev.jxbrowser.chromium

Class JSValue

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.teamdev.jxbrowser.chromium.JSValue
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    JSArray, JSDictionary, JSObject

    public class JSValue
extends java.lang.Object
    Class for all JavaScript values. This class is used to store the result of the Browser.executeJavaScriptAndReturnValue(String) method execution.

      • create

        public static JSValue create(JSValue... values)
        Creates JSArray from the list of passed values. If the list of passed values is empty, this method will create empty JSArray.
        Parameters:
        values - array of JSValue items. Cannot be null.
        Returns:
        JSArray that contains passed JSValue items.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when values is null.

      • create

        public static JSValue create(java.lang.Iterable iterable)
        Creates JSArray from the passed iterable. All values from the iterable will be wrapped into JSValue and added to the result JSArray in the same order. If method fails to convert iterable element to JSValue, an exception will be thrown.
        Parameters:
        iterable - contains values that will be wrapped into JSArray. It must contain the following types: JSValue, Boolean, Number, String. If iterable contains unsupported type, an exception will be thrown. Cannot be null.
        Returns:
        array of JSValue items received from iterable.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when iterable is null or contains unsupported types.

      • create

        public static JSValue create(java.util.Map map)
        Creates JSDictionary from the passed map. All values from the map will be wrapped into JSValue and added to the result JSDictionary. If method fails to convert map key/value to JSValue, an exception will be thrown.
        Parameters:
        map - contains key/value elements that will be wrapped into JSDictionary. The key/values must be one of the following types: JSValue, Boolean, Number, String. Cannot be null.
        Returns:
        dictionary of JSValue key/value pairs received from the map.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when map is null, or contains unsupported types.

        public boolean getBoolean()
        Returns value of JavaScript Boolean value. Before using this method make sure that this JavaScript value represents a boolean value via isBoolean() method. If the JavaScript value is not a Boolean value, then this method by default returns false.
        Returns:
        value of JavaScript Boolean value.

      • getNumber

        public double getNumber()
        Returns value of JavaScript Number value. Before using this method make sure that this JavaScript value represents Number value via isNumber() method. If the JavaScript value is not a Number value, then this method by default returns 0.0.
        Returns:
        value of JavaScript Number value.
